## Schema Rules

Table and field definitions must match **Engineering Action Plan v2.0 §4** (users, students,
behavioral incidents, sessions, success plans with milestones JSON, ai analyses). The measurement
model is incident-based; there is no CASEL 1–5 session score column.

### All Tables Use UUIDs

```prisma
model Student {
  id  String  @id @default(uuid())
  // ...
}
```

No auto-increment integers for primary keys. UUIDs prevent enumeration attacks on student records.

### Enum Values — snake_case Lowercase

```prisma
enum UserRole {
  owner
  assistant
  counselor
}

enum IncidentType {
  office_referral
  suspension_iss
  suspension_oss
  teacher_referral
  behavioral_incident
  other
}

enum Severity {
  low
  medium
  high
}
```

### Computed Fields — Schema Comment Required

Any field computed server-side must have a schema comment marking it as never written from the client:

```prisma
model Session {
  // ...
  goals_attempted      Int?    // COMPUTED server-side — never written from client
  goals_met            Int?    // COMPUTED server-side — never written from client
  goal_completion_rate Float?  // COMPUTED server-side — never written from client. goals_met / goals_attempted * 100
}
```

### JSON Fields — Explicitly Typed in Application Code

Prisma returns JSON fields as `Prisma.JsonValue`. Always cast to the explicit type on read:

```typescript
// types/session.ts
export type SessionGoal = {
  goal: string
  met: boolean
}

// In route handler
const goals = session.session_goals as SessionGoal[] | null
```

### Timestamps

All tables include `created_at`. Tables with mutable records include `updated_at`.

```prisma
created_at  DateTime  @default(now())
updated_at  DateTime  @updatedAt
```

